\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\n    \"rrt_max\", \n    \"checkoutservice->emailservice\", \n    \"checkoutservice->cartservice\", \n    \"cartservice->redis\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"EmailService\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Normal: 682.65 ms, Anomaly: 4458.00 ms\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"CartService\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Normal: 2592.54 ms, Anomaly: 23704.00 ms\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"Redis\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Normal: 1739.74 ms, Anomaly: 23043.00 ms\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```", "metric_analysis_findings": "Upon analyzing the provided metrics data, several anomalies have been identified. Here is the summary of the discovered abnormalities:\n\n### Detected Metric Keys\nThese are the metrics that showed significant deviation during the fault period:\n- `error_ratio`\n- `client_error_ratio`\n- `io_util`\n- `rrt_max`\n- `node_memory_usage_rate`\n- `node_filesystem_free_bytes`\n- `region_pending`\n\n### Key Findings and Hypotheses\n\n1. **TiDB IO Issues:**\n   - **Component:** `tidb-tikv`\n   - **Reason:** Abnormal increase in `io_util` indicating potential IO bottleneck.\n   - **Evidence:** `io_util` median ratio showed an increase from 0.08 to 0.36, and a P99 increase to 1.2717 times the normal.\n\n2. **Service Performance Issues:**\n\n   - **Adservice:**\n     - **Component:** `adservice-0`\n     - **Reason:** Significant spike in `error_ratio` and `client_error_ratio`.\n     - **Evidence:** Both metrics had a P99 change ratio of 2.0.\n\n   - **Currencyservice:**\n     - **Component:** `currencyservice-2`\n     - **Reason:** An increase in `rrt_max`, suggesting delayed response times.\n     - **Evidence:** `rrt_max` median changed from 4284.0 to 4547.0.\n\n   - **Paymentservice:**\n     - **Component:** `paymentservice-1`\n     - **Reason:** `rrt_max` and `rrt` showed noticeable increases.\